[[File:JuliaCseko-AConeyIslandOfTheMind-MM2006.jpg|thumb|Julia Csekö, "A Coney Island of the Mind-Marshal McLuhan," 2006, acrylic on canvas, 130.0 x 130.0 cm. Collection of the Morris and Helen Belkin Art Gallery, The University of British Columbia. Photo: Howard Ursuliak]]
'''Julia Csekö''' is an artist and art educator at the [[Museum of Fine Arts, Boston]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mfa.org/programs/community-programs/artful-adventures/about-instructors|title=About the Artful Adventures Instructors|date=2011-08-25|work=Museum of Fine Arts, Boston|access-date=2017-03-24|language=en}}</ref>

== Early life and education ==
She was born in Colorado and grew up in [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artsandbusinesscouncil.org/event/julia-cseko-straight-from-the-heart-the-rant-series/|title=Julia Csekö: Straight from the Heart – the Rant Series – Arts & Business Council of Boston|website=artsandbusinesscouncil.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-03-24}}</ref> She received a MFA, from the [[School of the Museum of Fine Arts at Tufts|School of the Museum of Fine Arts]] at Tufts University 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.smfa.edu/news/show/title/julia-cseko-mfa-13-1454534697-0.93624300/src/@random524c72a4c8b42|title=Julia Cseko (MFA ’13)|website=www.smfa.edu|access-date=2017-03-24}}</ref>

== Awards ==
She is the recipient of the 2015/16 Walter Feldman Fellowship for Emerging Artists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artsandbusinesscouncil.org/event/julia-cseko-straight-from-the-heart-the-rant-series/|title=Julia Csekö: Straight from the Heart – the Rant Series – Arts & Business Council of Boston|website=artsandbusinesscouncil.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-03-24}}</ref> The fellowship culminated in her first American, solo exhibition Straight from the Heart—The Rant Series.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zine.artscopemagazine.com/2016/08/art-that-can-talk-julia-cseko-at-piano-craft-gallery/|title=Art That Can Talk: Julia Csekö at Piano Craft Gallery|access-date=2017-03-24|language=en}}</ref>

