{{third-party|date=January 2015}}
'''Orange Pippin''' is a website providing information on the different cultivars of [[apple]], [[cherry]] and [[plum]]s. It was established around 2005 by Richard Borrie, a database programmer who lives in England.<ref>[http://www.orangepippin.com/resources/about-us About us]</ref>  Currently, it carries a listing of over 2000 apple orchards and 600 apple cultivars,<ref>[http://www.orangepippin.com/ Orange Pippin]</ref> and it is regarded as the most comprehensive resource for [[apple cultivars]] and orchards.<ref>[http://www.deeprootsathome.com/apples-orange-pippin-and-my-pixies/ Deep Roots]</ref>

Orange Pippin is named after [[England]]'s most famous apple variety, the [[Cox's Orange Pippin]] which according to them, is widely regarded as the finest of all dessert apples.<ref>[http://www.orangepippin.com/ Orange Pippin]</ref>

